# Chief Updates

## v3.1.1-dev

- **FIX**: Badge configuration after next-dev bump
- **CLEAN**: Removed unnecessary plugin descriptions from help output  
- **ENHANCED**: Added "Enterprise-Ready Tools" feature highlight to Key Features section

## v3.1.0

### üîí SSL/TLS Certificate Management
- **NEW**: `chief.ssl_create_ca` - Simple CA creation with minimal requirements  
- **NEW**: `chief.ssl_create_tls_cert` - Easy certificate creation signed by your CA
- **NEW**: `chief.ssl_view_cert` - Comprehensive certificate analysis with multiple display options
- **NEW**: `chief.ssl_get_cert` - Download certificates from remote servers with chain support
- **ENHANCED**: Rich help documentation and error handling for certificate operations
- **FIX**: macOS timeout command compatibility and certificate chain downloads

### ‚ò∏Ô∏è OpenShift Management Enhancements  
- **ENHANCED**: `chief.oc_show_stuck_resources` - Added `--fix` option to automatically remove finalizers
- **NEW**: `chief.oc_delete_stuck_ns` - Force delete stuck terminating namespaces using Red Hat methodology
- **ENHANCED**: `chief.oc_approve_csrs` - Complete rewrite with interactive/batch modes and filtering
- **ENHANCED**: `chief.oc_get_all_objects` - Complete rewrite with filtering and output formats
- **ENHANCED**: `chief.oc_clean_olm` - Enhanced OLM cleanup with selective targeting and dry-run modes
- **ENHANCED**: `chief.oc_clean_replicasets` - Advanced ReplicaSet cleanup with age filtering
- **ENHANCED**: Professional terminal colors and attribution to Red Hat techniques

### üõ†Ô∏è System Utilities Enhancement
- **NEW**: `chief.etc_folder_sync` - Professional-grade directory synchronization using rsync
- **ENHANCED**: `chief.etc_create_bootusb` - Complete safety overhaul with multi-platform support and dry-run
- **ENHANCED**: `chief.etc_copy_dotfiles` - Enhanced dotfiles management with backup options
- **ENHANCED**: `chief.etc_chmod_f` and `chief.etc_chmod_d` - Enhanced file permission management with validation

### üñ•Ô∏è Modern Terminal Multiplexer Support
- **NEW**: tmux-based shared terminals (replaced archaic GNU Screen)
- **ENHANCED**: Better multi-user support with read-only observer mode
- **NEW**: Session listing and detached session creation capabilities
- **ENHANCED**: Built-in tmux key binding reference and session management tips

### üõ°Ô∏è Enhanced Safety Features
- **NEW**: Dry-run support for critical operations (`chief.etc_create_bootusb -n`, `chief.git_reset-hard -n`)
- **ENHANCED**: Comprehensive preview showing exact commands and affected files
- **SAFETY**: Zero risk testing with validation before execution

### üîê Air-Gapped Installation Support
- **NEW**: `./tools/install.sh --local` - Install from local files in disconnected environments
- **SECURITY**: No internet required during installation with complete file transparency
- **ENHANCED**: Manual update control for security compliance

### üèóÔ∏è Development & Quality Improvements
- **REFACTOR**: All 39 private functions now use `__chief_*` prefix (prevents conflicts with other utilities)
- **NEW**: GitHub Actions CI/CD integration with automated testing on main/dev branches
- **NEW**: Comprehensive test suite with syntax, plugin, and integration validation
- **ENHANCED**: Version management with development workflow and release automation
- **FIX**: `__chief.bump next-dev` validation now accepts `-dev` version suffixes
- **NEW**: Test validation integrated into release workflows - tests must pass before releases
- **ENHANCED**: Context-aware completion messages and version-specific release notes structure
- **FIX**: Badge management system separating release badges from development badges
- **ENHANCED**: User experience with comprehensive bug reporting guidance and OS detection

